<p>evaluate reliability of recognition results.</p>

<h3 id="why-measure-confidence-or-reliability">Why measure confidence or reliability?</h3>
<p>ambient noises, speaker variations, channel distortions and other mismatches.</p>

<h3 id="major-methods-in-category">Major methods in category?</h3>
<ol>
  <li>combination of predictor features;
    <ul>
      <li>log-likelihoods,</li>
      <li>word duration</li>
      <li>word graph density</li>
      <li></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>posterior probability: estimate the probability of the sequence given the acoustic observations.</li>
  <li>hypothesis testing: likelihood ratio = (word likelihood score) / (background model + competing model)</li>
  <li>utterance verification.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="specific-name">Specific Name</h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    <h2 id="non-keyword-rejection-or-keyword-recognition-detect-if-the-input-speech-does-not-contain-any-of-the-words-in-the-recognizer-vocabulary-set"><em>non-keyword rejection</em> or <em>keyword recognition</em>: detect if the input speech does not contain any of the words in the recognizer vocabulary set.</h2>
  </li>
</ul>

